
## LANDING 3 — SCARLET DEVIL MANSION

The foyer is enormous and red and very quiet.

Dozens of identical fairy maids stop moving at exactly the same moment. Every head turns. The players are standing on a marble floor under a chandelier that is definitely magical and definitely expensive, and the silence has the specific quality of a room that was in motion one second ago and is now holding very, very still.

Then she's simply there.

Silver hair. A uniform that means business. Five throwing knives held between her fingers with the casualness of someone who has done this ten thousand times and will do it ten thousand more.

She looks at the players the way a person looks at a problem they are deciding how to categorize.

> "You have approximately ten seconds to explain what you're doing in this foyer before I make a decision about you."

Her name is Sakuya Izayoi. She is the head maid of this mansion. She is being polite. This is what polite looks like here.

> **DM:** What do you say?

*However the players handle this — calm, panicked, honest, confused — Sakuya listens. She doesn't react much. When they finish, she puts the knives away.*

> "The Mistress will want to see you."

*This is not a question.*

